Production numbers were, four-door sedan = 491,441; two-door sedan = 256,182; four-door station wagon = 170,473; sport coupe = 142,592; sport sedan = 83,330; convertible = 55,989; two-door station wagon = 16,590. VIN Numbers Serial Numbers were stamped on a plate on the left front door hinge pillar (center pillar on Corvair and on the driver-side door post on Corvette). The Fisher Body number plate on the right-hand side of the cowl gives additional information such as the body style number, the production sequence number, the trim (upholstery) number code and the paint number code.
